Travel Booking System
A comprehensive Java-based travel booking system that allows users to search, book, and manage travel arrangements including flights, hotels, and car rentals.
Features

User Management

User registration and authentication
Profile management
Password recovery


Search Functionality

Advanced flight search with multiple filters
Hotel search with amenity filters
Car rental search with vehicle type filters
Real-time availability checking


Booking Management

Create, view, modify, and cancel bookings
Booking confirmation emails
Booking history
Multi-service bookings (flight + hotel + car)


Payment System

Multiple payment method support
Secure transaction processing
Refund handling
Payment history


Review System

Rate and review services
View aggregate ratings
Filter reviews by rating/date


Recommendations

Personalized travel suggestions
Based on booking history and preferences
Trending destinations


Notifications

Booking confirmations
Travel alerts
Promotional offers
Price drop alerts



Technical Requirements

Java JDK 11 or higher
MySQL 8.0 or higher
Maven 3.6 or higher
SMTP server for email notifications

Dependencies
xmlCopy<dependencies>
    <!-- MySQL Connector -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>mysql</groupId>
        <artifactId>mysql-connector-java</artifactId>
        <version>8.0.27</version>
    </dependency>
    
    <!-- JavaMail API -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>javax.mail</groupId>
        <artifactId>javax.mail-api</artifactId>
        <version>1.6.2</version>
    </dependency>
    
    <!-- For secure password hashing -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.mindrot</groupId>
        <artifactId>jbcrypt</artifactId>
        <version>0.4</version>
    </dependency>
</dependencies>
Installation

Clone the repository:
bashCopygit clone https://github.com/yourusername/travel-booking-system.git
cd travel-booking-system

Set up the database:
bashCopymysql -u root -p < database/schema.sql

Configure the application:

Copy config/application.properties.example to config/application.properties
Update database credentials and other configuration settings


Build the project:
bashCopymvn clean install

Run the application:
bashCopyjava -jar target/travel-booking-system.jar


